WEBVTT

00:01.262 --> 00:02.567
Previously onLucifer...

00:02.611 --> 00:04.178
We need to figure out
who kidnapped me.

00:04.221 --> 00:05.962
I'm fairly certain that
my Father's behind it.

00:06.006 --> 00:07.355
AMENADIEL: Lucifer,
I'm not angry with you,

00:07.398 --> 00:08.704
that you somehow
got your wings back,

00:08.747 --> 00:10.749
or even that
you cut them off again.

00:10.793 --> 00:12.534
I was tested once,
and I failed.

00:12.577 --> 00:13.796
I'm not gonna fail again.

00:13.839 --> 00:16.016
I suppose this won't bother you.

00:16.842 --> 00:17.800
But you cut them off.

00:17.843 --> 00:18.975
The pesky things seem to be

00:19.019 --> 00:20.846
a bit more tenacious
this time around.

00:20.890 --> 00:22.196
I'm Lieutenant Marcus Pierce.

00:22.239 --> 00:23.806
DAN: Heard a lot about
you, Lieutenant,

00:23.849 --> 00:25.286
and I'm really excited
to work with you.

00:25.329 --> 00:27.114
Aren't you that corrupt
cop that got off easy?

00:27.157 --> 00:28.245
Excuse me?

00:28.289 --> 00:29.507
People come to me
to ask for favors,

00:29.551 --> 00:31.205
and more often than not,
I'm happy to oblige.

00:31.248 --> 00:32.380
What do you get?

00:32.423 --> 00:34.730
Simply to be repaid
at a later date.

00:34.773 --> 00:37.515
A devilish IOU, if you will.

00:37.559 --> 00:39.735
LUCIFER:
Who's the Sinnerman?

00:39.778 --> 00:41.215
That's who hired me
to kidnap you.

00:41.258 --> 00:43.652
He's a scary dude.
Huge crime boss.

00:43.695 --> 00:44.827
And where do I find him?

00:44.870 --> 00:48.048
SAM:
You don't. He finds you.

00:49.179 --> 00:51.399
♪

00:51.442 --> 00:54.358
♪ Down, down, d-down, down ♪ Are you?♪

00:57.187 --> 00:59.972
♪ Down, down, d-d-down,
down, down, down ♪

01:00.016 --> 01:02.279
♪ Are you down, are you down,
are you d-d-down? ♪

01:02.323 --> 01:05.239
♪ Are you down, are you
down, are you d-d-d-d-down? ♪

01:05.282 --> 01:07.110
♪ Are you...

01:07.154 --> 01:08.807
This way.

01:08.851 --> 01:10.896
[vocalizing]

01:10.940 --> 01:13.029
♪ Down

01:13.073 --> 01:14.900
♪ Are you, are you

01:14.944 --> 01:17.294
♪ D-D-D-D-Down, are you...

01:17.338 --> 01:18.817
[vocalizing]

01:18.861 --> 01:20.297
Ah...

01:21.994 --> 01:24.301
[sighs]
You're an angel.

01:24.345 --> 01:25.824
[Lucifer sighs]

01:25.868 --> 01:27.261
Oh, gosh.

01:27.304 --> 01:28.523
Uh, my apologies.

01:28.566 --> 01:30.481
And for the record,
I don't usually suffer

01:30.525 --> 01:33.049
from premature unfurling.

01:33.093 --> 01:34.485
[grunts, chuckles]

01:34.529 --> 01:37.140
Right.
Now, where were we?

01:37.184 --> 01:39.403
No, keep them out.

01:39.447 --> 01:42.493
I'm totally into cosplay.

01:42.537 --> 01:45.670
I could dress up as a devil
and make it really sexy.

01:45.714 --> 01:50.240
I have no desire
to have sex with myself.

01:50.284 --> 01:52.634
Not right now, at least.

01:52.677 --> 01:54.070
Where are you going?

01:54.114 --> 01:56.290
To do some grooming.

01:56.333 --> 01:59.380
[sighs]

01:59.423 --> 02:00.903
I'd recommend you leave. Now.

02:02.687 --> 02:04.211
I'm about to engage
in a rather gruesome form

02:04.254 --> 02:05.560
of manscaping.

02:05.603 --> 02:07.127
LINDA:
You cut them off, didn't you?

02:07.170 --> 02:09.259
I did, yes.

02:09.303 --> 02:11.435
But then they grew back,
so I cut them off again.

02:11.479 --> 02:13.089
It's like whack-a-mole
back there.

02:13.133 --> 02:14.569
[chuckles]

02:14.612 --> 02:16.092
I'm worried about you.

02:16.136 --> 02:19.487
What you're describing
is self-mutilation.

02:19.530 --> 02:22.229
Doctor, someone is
forcing those wings on me.

02:22.272 --> 02:24.274
They took away my devil face.

02:24.318 --> 02:26.711
And I won't stand for someone
making me something I'm not.

02:28.713 --> 02:30.889
Are you any closer to
finding out who did this?

02:30.933 --> 02:33.675
Yes. Well, a little.

02:33.718 --> 02:36.199
He calls himself
"The Sinnerman."

02:36.243 --> 02:37.722
From what I can gather,

02:37.766 --> 02:40.334
he's a criminal mastermind
who just moved his operation

02:40.377 --> 02:42.901
to Los Angeles, but no one
seems to have ever met him,

02:42.945 --> 02:45.600
which makes punching him in the
face frustratingly difficult.

02:45.643 --> 02:47.950
Well, maybe... [groans]

02:47.993 --> 02:49.299
Doctor,

02:49.343 --> 02:50.996
are you sure you're all right
to be back at work?

02:51.040 --> 02:52.346
I mean, it really
hasn't been that long

02:52.389 --> 02:53.782
since Mum flambéed you.

02:53.825 --> 02:56.567
Yes. It certainly was a...

02:56.611 --> 02:58.221
traumatic experience.

02:58.265 --> 03:00.136
Fortunately, I'm trained to deal
with that sort of thing,

03:00.180 --> 03:01.355
and I'm doing just that.

03:01.398 --> 03:03.531
And there's nothing
I can do to help?

03:03.574 --> 03:05.924
Yes. You can let me
get back to you.

03:05.968 --> 03:08.144
Oh, if you insist.

03:08.188 --> 03:11.756
Oh, I haven't even told you
the worst part, have I?

03:11.800 --> 03:13.541
Not only did he stick
my wings back on

03:13.584 --> 03:16.065
and take my face,
he's stolen my shtick as well.

03:17.414 --> 03:18.546
He gives out favors to people

03:18.589 --> 03:20.417
for a price to be named later.

03:20.461 --> 03:21.984
Sound familiar?

03:22.027 --> 03:26.336
Lucifer, you didn't invent
the idea of giving out favors.

03:26.380 --> 03:29.339
[chuckles] Yep,
forgot who I was talking to.

03:29.383 --> 03:31.385
I suppose you did.

03:31.428 --> 03:33.648
But you haven't given
out favors in a while.

03:33.691 --> 03:35.215
And the Sinnerman knows it.

03:35.258 --> 03:37.042
I think he's
taunting me.

03:37.086 --> 03:38.392
Do you think he's human?

03:38.435 --> 03:39.958
Or something else?

03:40.002 --> 03:41.743
I don't know.

03:41.786 --> 03:45.268
But whatever he is, I'm gonna
stop at nothing to find him.

03:45.312 --> 03:46.356
CHLOE:
We found him.

03:46.400 --> 03:48.358
LUCIFER:
Who? The missing link?

03:48.402 --> 03:50.534
Proof of human-rodent
copulation.

03:50.578 --> 03:51.927
It's Mike Alonso.

03:51.970 --> 03:53.711
The guy that skewered your
kidnapper under the pier.

03:53.755 --> 03:56.279
[scoffs] This is clearly
not the Sinnerman.

03:56.323 --> 03:58.281
Clearly not,
since I'm pretty sure

03:58.325 --> 04:00.109
that no one with that name
actually exists.

04:00.152 --> 04:02.938
He had motive, no alibi,

04:02.981 --> 04:05.070
and, oh, yeah,
he confessed

04:05.114 --> 04:06.942
under interrogation.
He's our guy.

04:06.985 --> 04:08.683
Well, then he must be
working for the Sinnerman.

04:09.858 --> 04:11.294
You're not gonna drag me

04:11.338 --> 04:13.078
into whatever new
weird drama this is.

04:13.122 --> 04:14.689
And could you please

04:14.732 --> 04:16.168
stop saying "Sinnerman"?

04:16.212 --> 04:17.474
Sinnerman.

04:18.910 --> 04:20.434
Big Nina Simone fan?

04:20.477 --> 04:21.609
Well, actually, I am.
But I was just sayingWhat? Nothing.

04:21.652 --> 04:22.827
to the detective...Nothing. It's nothing.

04:24.525 --> 04:26.831
Are you hiding something
from me, Detective?

04:26.875 --> 04:29.747
No.

04:29.791 --> 04:31.358
I don't care;
I was just asking.

04:31.401 --> 04:34.056
New case came in,
you're up.

04:34.099 --> 04:35.144
Thank you.

04:35.187 --> 04:36.711
[sighs]

04:36.754 --> 04:39.322
Okay. Why did you just stop me
telling the new lieutenant

04:39.366 --> 04:41.150
we're on the cusp of the
greatest case of our lives?

04:41.193 --> 04:44.545
Because the Sinnerman is an
urban myth; he doesn't exist.

04:44.588 --> 04:46.329
He's a boogeyman
that criminals use

04:46.373 --> 04:47.635
to hide their bad behavior.

04:47.678 --> 04:49.289
"Oh, the Sinnerman
made me do it."

04:49.332 --> 04:50.725
Yet another thing
he's stolen from me,

04:50.768 --> 04:53.293
being blamed for
the bad deeds of men.

04:53.336 --> 04:55.643
He can keep that one, actually.[scoffs] So the idea

04:55.686 --> 04:58.080
of telling our new boss--

04:58.123 --> 05:00.169
who I'm just starting
to get a rhythm with--

05:00.212 --> 05:02.345
that you want to arrest
the Easter Bunny

05:02.389 --> 05:03.738
doesn't really thrill me.

05:03.781 --> 05:05.217
I have no intention
of arresting anyone.

05:05.261 --> 05:06.915
I want to grab him by his
neck and see what happens

05:06.958 --> 05:08.351
when I squeeze hard enough.

05:08.395 --> 05:12.312
If you can bring me
any tiny bit of evidence

05:12.355 --> 05:13.922
that the Sinnerman
actually exists,

05:13.965 --> 05:15.489
I will be the first
to look into it.

05:15.532 --> 05:17.360
But...

05:17.404 --> 05:21.233
until then,
consider this case closed.

05:21.277 --> 05:23.192
And let's focus
on this case, please.

05:23.235 --> 05:24.411
Okay.

05:24.454 --> 05:25.803
♪ Ah, ah, ah

05:25.847 --> 05:28.371
♪ Ah-ah, ah, ah, ah-ah ♪ Come on♪

05:28.415 --> 05:30.634
♪ I'm gonna handcuff lightning

05:30.678 --> 05:34.551
♪ Throw thunder in the ring

05:34.595 --> 05:36.510
♪ Won't slack,
won't turn my back ♪

05:36.553 --> 05:39.730
♪ I'll get on my knees
and pray ♪[train horn blows]

05:39.774 --> 05:43.386
♪ My heart beats
strong as rock ♪

05:43.430 --> 05:45.519
♪ My blood runs cold and hot

05:45.562 --> 05:48.522
♪ My eyes see what you got

05:48.565 --> 05:51.176
♪ I'll get on my knees
and pray ♪

05:51.220 --> 05:53.353
LUCIFER:
[whistles] Daniel?

05:53.396 --> 05:55.659
Guy's name
is JD Woodstock.

05:55.703 --> 05:57.487
He lived right
around the corner.

05:57.531 --> 05:59.141
Neighbors said he
was pretty quiet.

05:59.184 --> 06:00.708
Unemployed, but we
found this on him.

06:00.751 --> 06:02.449
Huh.

06:04.755 --> 06:06.061
So what are these? Jokes?

06:06.104 --> 06:08.542
A charitable description,
Detective.

06:08.585 --> 06:09.543
"Avocado?

06:09.586 --> 06:11.545
How about avoca-don't?"

06:11.588 --> 06:13.242
Would it be rude
to throw tomatoes at a corpse?

06:13.285 --> 06:15.070
DAN: Looks like he was
a struggling comedian.

06:15.113 --> 06:17.289
We're trying to figure out
if he performed anywhere.

06:17.333 --> 06:18.595
What'd he do? Make
fun of the wrong person?

06:18.639 --> 06:20.031
Get in a fight with
an audience member?

06:20.075 --> 06:21.685
It's worth exploring,
at least.

06:21.729 --> 06:23.513
You know, there are a lot
of insult comics out there,

06:23.557 --> 06:25.472
and not everybody
enjoys being mocked.

06:25.515 --> 06:26.995
Hmm. We should listen
to Daniel, actually.

06:27.038 --> 06:28.649
He's got a unique
insight into this case.

06:28.692 --> 06:30.433
What's he talking about?

06:30.477 --> 06:31.652
Well, they're
kindred spirits.

06:31.695 --> 06:33.610
A fellow broken
soul who puts

06:33.654 --> 06:35.003
the most embarrassing parts
of his life on display

06:35.046 --> 06:36.439
for his audience
for an easy laugh.

06:36.483 --> 06:38.702
He does stand-up;
I do improv.

06:38.746 --> 06:39.790
They're completely
different things.

06:39.834 --> 06:41.139
Oh.
Improv

06:41.183 --> 06:42.663
is all about "yes, and."

06:42.706 --> 06:44.055
Stand-up, well, that's about
telling jokes...

06:44.099 --> 06:45.840
I-I regret starting
this entire conversation.

06:45.883 --> 06:48.059
Wait. Excuse me, Dan.

06:48.103 --> 06:49.234
You do improv?

06:49.278 --> 06:51.802
How did I not know that?
And how did he?

06:51.846 --> 06:53.587
Well, it's a funny story,
actually.Actually,

06:53.630 --> 06:55.284
it's because I-I don't
tell a lot of people.

06:55.327 --> 06:56.241
Why?

06:56.285 --> 06:57.808
Yeah-- hey, Ella.

06:57.852 --> 06:59.593
How's it going?
What'd you find?

06:59.636 --> 07:02.639
Well, no murder weapon, but I
did find three shell casings.

07:02.683 --> 07:04.641
Running ballistics
on them now.

07:04.685 --> 07:07.383
But, based on the
firing pattern,

07:07.427 --> 07:10.734
I think this dude was tortured
before he finally died.

07:10.778 --> 07:12.649
Oh, well congratulations,
Mr. Woodstock.

07:12.693 --> 07:14.738
At least someone cared enough
about your jokes to...

07:14.782 --> 07:15.739
ELLA: Did you just
say Woodstock?

07:15.783 --> 07:18.176
As in, JD Woodstock?

07:18.220 --> 07:19.395
Yeah. Why?
You know him?

07:19.439 --> 07:20.614
Yeah. He made big news
a couple days ago,

07:20.657 --> 07:22.529
claiming Bobby Lowe
stole his jokes.

07:22.572 --> 07:24.661
And who is Bobby Lowe?
A rival comedian

07:24.705 --> 07:26.750
who hates himself so much
he stole this drivel?

07:26.794 --> 07:29.884
Uh, no.

07:29.927 --> 07:31.625
Open your eyes, pal.

07:31.668 --> 07:34.062
Yeah. JD claimed
that Bobby's show

07:34.105 --> 07:35.498
was based on
his own material.

07:35.542 --> 07:36.673
And that he
could prove it.

07:36.717 --> 07:38.370
Which is impossible,

07:38.414 --> 07:40.677
because Bobby Lowe's show
is all about his life.

07:40.721 --> 07:42.636
Wait, so you're saying that
this giant-headed buffoon

07:42.679 --> 07:44.681
stole our poor
victim's ideas?

07:44.725 --> 07:46.944
His life's work
and built a business out of it?

07:46.988 --> 07:49.773
Mm. So now he's a "poor victim."

07:49.817 --> 07:51.601
Look, I know you don't
believe me, Detective,

07:51.645 --> 07:53.516
but I happen to be going through
something quite similar,

07:53.560 --> 07:54.865
so if I can't get
my own justice,

07:54.909 --> 07:58.565
I'm gonna get it for
this poor unfunny soul.

07:58.608 --> 08:01.393
Well, I certainly did want you
to focus on this case,

08:01.437 --> 08:03.134
but be careful
what you wish for.

08:03.178 --> 08:05.528
At least the lieutenant
isn't here.

08:05.572 --> 08:08.313
You know, if you keep saying
crazy things around him,

08:08.357 --> 08:10.098
[over microphone]:
who knows what he might do.

08:10.141 --> 08:12.535
Right. When have I ever
cared about that, Detective?

08:12.579 --> 08:14.102
Ah, that's true.[chuckles]

08:14.145 --> 08:15.799
[indistinct conversation
continues over microphone]

08:18.802 --> 08:20.761
♪

08:29.465 --> 08:31.119
JD:
I sweated over every joke.

08:31.162 --> 08:33.425
Worked my ass off for months.

08:33.469 --> 08:36.516
And Bobby stole it all
like it was nothing.

08:36.559 --> 08:40.694
Created a show
based on my jokes!

08:40.737 --> 08:42.696
Well Bobby, guess what?

08:42.739 --> 08:44.436
I finally found it.

08:44.480 --> 08:47.135
Proof you're a fraud.

08:47.178 --> 08:51.487
And I'm going to show it
to the world.

08:51.531 --> 08:54.577
Well? Which of these boxes
do I click on for the proof?

08:54.621 --> 08:56.753
None. He posted this video
the day before he died.

08:56.797 --> 08:59.234
And we can't find whatever proof
he claimed to have had.

08:59.277 --> 09:01.149
So that's why JD
was tortured,

09:01.192 --> 09:02.977
so the killer could
find and destroy it?

09:03.020 --> 09:05.588
ELLA: [coughs]
Or he's a liar.

09:05.632 --> 09:07.503
Huh?

09:07.547 --> 09:08.809
I'm not sure who said that,

09:08.852 --> 09:12.639
but I totally agree with them.

09:12.682 --> 09:14.684
Bobby Lowe would never
do something like that.

09:14.728 --> 09:16.381
Why do you say that?
Because,

09:16.425 --> 09:18.645
Bobby's show is so personal.

09:18.688 --> 09:20.081
It's so authentic.

09:20.124 --> 09:21.517
There's no way that
you could fake it.

09:21.561 --> 09:22.649
Right. Don't listen to her.

09:22.692 --> 09:23.867
The man is
clearly a thief.

09:23.911 --> 09:25.216
Let's go give him
a good throttling.

09:25.260 --> 09:27.001
CHLOE: I'm leaning towards
just talking to him.

09:27.044 --> 09:28.176
And then throttling.
I suppose a little foreplay

09:28.219 --> 09:29.394
never hurt anyone.

09:29.438 --> 09:30.570
Wait.

09:30.613 --> 09:31.788
Wait, wait, wait, wait.
You guys are gonna

09:31.832 --> 09:33.834
go talk to him, like,
right now this second?

09:33.877 --> 09:35.096
Yeah. Why?

09:35.139 --> 09:36.793
Maybe I should go with.

09:36.837 --> 09:40.014
You know, to collect
the evidence.

09:40.057 --> 09:42.886
Right. Well, if
he's innocent...He's not innocent.

09:42.930 --> 09:45.628
If he's innocent,
then there won't

09:45.672 --> 09:47.195
be any evidence
to collect,

09:47.238 --> 09:49.023
so probably better
if you hang here.

09:49.066 --> 09:52.026
Yeah. I-I see what
you're saying there,

09:52.069 --> 09:53.027
but...

09:53.070 --> 09:54.811
I just think, to be safe,

09:54.855 --> 09:57.205
I should collect
as much stuff as possible.

09:57.248 --> 09:59.207
You know, fingerprints,
a lock of hair, an autograph.

09:59.250 --> 10:00.643
Right.

10:00.687 --> 10:02.819
To be safe.

10:02.863 --> 10:04.691
Okay.

10:04.734 --> 10:06.127
To be safe.

10:06.170 --> 10:08.085
Yeah!

10:10.392 --> 10:12.568
♪ Lipstick stuck on

10:12.612 --> 10:14.657
♪ High heels sharpened

10:14.701 --> 10:16.572
♪ Eyes lined, it's on

10:16.616 --> 10:19.270
♪ Think it's time to
get my walk on... ♪

10:19.314 --> 10:20.750
Hey.

10:20.794 --> 10:22.926
Hey.

10:22.970 --> 10:24.101
Yeah.

10:24.145 --> 10:25.886
Thanks for meeting
me, Amenadiel.

10:25.929 --> 10:28.149
Is there a shorter version
of that?

10:28.192 --> 10:30.586
Does anyone ever
call you "Amen"?

10:30.630 --> 10:31.674
[chuckles]

10:31.718 --> 10:33.023
Probably not.

10:33.067 --> 10:34.677
Oh, you would be the first.

10:34.721 --> 10:36.766
[laughs]

10:36.810 --> 10:38.028
So, Linda,
what's going on?

10:38.072 --> 10:42.206
Um, I just wanted
to say thank you.

10:43.294 --> 10:45.079
For saving my life.

10:45.122 --> 10:46.515
Maze is the one
who saved your life.

10:46.558 --> 10:47.864
And I thanked
her so much,

10:47.908 --> 10:49.300
I think she's avoiding me now.

10:51.172 --> 10:54.610
But I wouldn't be here
without you, too.

10:54.654 --> 10:57.091
I didn't do anything.

10:57.134 --> 10:59.354
Other than miraculously
slowing down time

10:59.397 --> 11:01.051
so that I didn't
bleed to death?

11:01.095 --> 11:02.966
Well, other than that.

11:03.010 --> 11:05.490
[chuckles]

11:05.534 --> 11:07.057
How are you really doing,
by the way?

11:07.101 --> 11:08.624
I'm fine.

11:10.757 --> 11:13.411
You have your powers back.

11:13.455 --> 11:14.630
That must be exciting.

11:14.674 --> 11:18.765
Mm. Um, not exactly.

11:18.808 --> 11:20.505
They haven't worked
since that day.

11:20.549 --> 11:23.247
I'm sorry to hear that.

11:23.291 --> 11:24.509
Ah, don't be.

11:24.553 --> 11:27.077
I think it's just my Father
testing me again.

11:27.121 --> 11:29.340
But this time,
Linda, I'm ready.

11:29.384 --> 11:30.777
How is He testing you?

11:32.909 --> 11:34.737
Do you have to
fight someone?

11:34.781 --> 11:36.696
Solve advanced
math problems?

11:36.739 --> 11:41.744
Well, if I'm right,
there's something I need to do

11:41.788 --> 11:44.225
in the penthouse and, uh...

11:44.268 --> 11:46.575
I've been avoiding it.

