38:00.452 --> 38:02.628
Also, I ran out,
but more importantly,

38:02.671 --> 38:04.107
did you text me to come here?

38:04.151 --> 38:05.848
I didn't recognize the number,
so I assumed it was you.

38:05.892 --> 38:07.197
You didn't save my number?

38:07.241 --> 38:08.329
PIERCE:
It was me.

38:18.121 --> 38:20.646
Too much hard work
to break into my penthouse again

38:20.689 --> 38:22.169
for a heart-to-heart?

38:22.212 --> 38:24.650
I did some digging,
and you were right.

38:24.693 --> 38:26.042
The Sinnerman is here in L.A.

38:26.086 --> 38:28.001
Oh, right.

38:28.044 --> 38:29.263
Are you not gonna
take my advice

38:29.307 --> 38:32.048
from last night?Most definitely not.

38:32.092 --> 38:33.572
I thought so.

38:38.490 --> 38:40.274
You brought the Sinnerman's
murderous thug in.

38:40.318 --> 38:43.364
PIERCE:
He's all yours.

38:43.408 --> 38:45.758
I couldn't get anything
out of him. Maybe you can.

38:45.801 --> 38:48.108
[laughing]:
Oh. Right.

38:48.151 --> 38:49.936
So, what, is this
you passing the baton?

38:49.979 --> 38:51.981
Where are you running
off to next?
Nowhere.

38:52.025 --> 38:53.505
I'm seeing this through.

38:53.548 --> 38:55.898
But you need to shut your
damn mouth about the Sinnerman.

38:55.942 --> 38:57.596
We need to play this carefully.

38:57.639 --> 38:59.162
Let's keep it between us.

38:59.206 --> 39:01.164
[scoffs]
The less people
who know about it,

39:01.208 --> 39:02.731
the less chance
anyone gets hurt.

39:02.775 --> 39:05.038
But the detective...Has a kid.

39:05.081 --> 39:07.649
She stays out of it.

39:09.825 --> 39:11.131
[sighs]

39:11.174 --> 39:12.872
Very well.

39:15.918 --> 39:17.790
[chuckles softly]

39:26.189 --> 39:28.540
Hello, Alonso.

39:28.583 --> 39:31.456
Let's cut to the
chase, shall we?

39:31.499 --> 39:34.807
I know the Sinnerman had you
skewer Sam under the pier,

39:34.850 --> 39:36.896
so tell me everything.

39:36.939 --> 39:38.463
Who the hell's the Sinnerman?

39:38.506 --> 39:41.291
[laughs]

39:41.335 --> 39:43.250
Fine.

39:43.293 --> 39:45.252
Fine. Let's play
a little game, shall we?

39:45.295 --> 39:46.384
Look at me.

39:48.255 --> 39:49.909
Tell me.

39:49.952 --> 39:54.435
Why did you really
desire Sam's death?

39:54.479 --> 39:57.960
I... didn't want my girl
to sleep with him anymore.

40:01.050 --> 40:02.356
And?

40:02.400 --> 40:05.228
And... that's it.

40:05.272 --> 40:07.230
I got pissed.

40:07.274 --> 40:09.407
Went medieval on his ass
to send a message.

40:09.450 --> 40:11.583
No one touches my girl.

40:11.626 --> 40:13.715
And what about the Sinnerman?

40:13.759 --> 40:15.891
Man, I have no idea
what you're talking about.

40:15.935 --> 40:17.676
Oh, you must know.
Come on, Alonso.

40:17.719 --> 40:19.242
What about the Sinnerman?

40:19.286 --> 40:20.809
I don't know.

40:20.853 --> 40:22.637
You must know!

40:24.552 --> 40:26.641
I don't know
anything... I swear.

40:28.861 --> 40:31.211
[swallows hard]

40:32.386 --> 40:34.127
I believe you.

40:38.871 --> 40:40.916
LUCIFER:
He was telling the truth.

40:40.960 --> 40:42.657
I mean, maybe

40:42.701 --> 40:45.443
the Sinnerman manipulated Alonso
without him realizing it.

40:45.486 --> 40:48.358
Or perhaps he was just
a deranged fellow who felt

40:48.402 --> 40:50.665
impaling a rival lover to death
was the way to his girl's heart.

40:52.406 --> 40:55.148
It's a bit old-fashioned,
really.

40:56.802 --> 40:58.978
Lucifer, I want
to talk about your wings.

40:59.021 --> 41:01.328
Oh, bloody hell.
They're not out again?!

41:01.371 --> 41:03.417
So they grew back?

41:04.549 --> 41:07.160
They did... this morning.

41:07.203 --> 41:09.075
Sneaky buggers.

41:09.118 --> 41:11.512
You can't keep doing this
to yourself.Oh, I agree.

41:11.556 --> 41:13.862
You do?
Yes.

41:13.906 --> 41:16.865
It's getting exhausting...
and quite messy.

41:16.909 --> 41:19.259
No, I need a new solution.

41:19.302 --> 41:21.957
Maybe I should hire someone
to do it.

41:22.001 --> 41:25.004
Or maybe your solution is

41:25.047 --> 41:28.573
to accept that, for now,
you have wings again.

41:28.616 --> 41:32.359
What, and let Dad win,
or whoever it bloody is?

41:32.402 --> 41:34.317
I... I don't think so.

41:36.363 --> 41:39.888
It's easy to let
external factors... define us.

41:39.932 --> 41:41.455
[clock ticking]

41:41.499 --> 41:43.413
Especially the traumatic ones.

41:44.980 --> 41:47.374
But only if we let them.

41:50.508 --> 41:52.597
We all have itchy butts.

41:52.640 --> 41:54.076
Excuse me?

41:54.120 --> 41:55.556
No, it's just something
a woman said to me

41:55.600 --> 41:57.036
right before
I punched her in the face.

41:59.212 --> 42:01.257
It's not about the idea.
It's about the execution.

42:01.301 --> 42:03.346
It's about how I usethe wings.

42:03.390 --> 42:05.827
That's... actually...

42:05.871 --> 42:07.829
pretty wise.

42:07.873 --> 42:09.527
Yeah. So I'll just
tuck them away

42:09.570 --> 42:11.354
and pretend they don't exist.Less good.

42:11.398 --> 42:13.269
Someone else is giving favors.
Who cares?

42:14.444 --> 42:16.403
I'm Lucifer bloody Morningstar!

42:16.446 --> 42:18.448
I do favors better
than anyone else.

42:18.492 --> 42:22.191
Amongst other things,
of course.

42:22.235 --> 42:24.324
Or at least, I used to.

42:24.367 --> 42:26.500
And I think that maybe...

42:28.371 --> 42:30.025
...it's about time
I got back in the game.

42:30.069 --> 42:32.114
♪

42:33.942 --> 42:35.770
♪ Please me

42:35.814 --> 42:40.296
♪ Oh, won't you
ever please me? ♪

42:40.340 --> 42:45.432
♪ You will give me the faith
and I'll bring it on ♪

42:45.475 --> 42:48.304
♪ There's a way
through the storm. ♪

42:55.921 --> 42:58.401
Hello.

42:59.881 --> 43:05.887
So, tell me. What is it
that you truly desire?
